import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['delay'], bins=30, edgecolor='black')
    plt.xlabel('Delay Time')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of delay time?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
        plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    avg_distance = data['distance'].mean()
    data['distance'].plot(kind='bar')
    
    plt.axhline(y=avg_distance, color='r', linestyle='-', label=f'Average Distance: {avg_distance:.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("What is the average distance traveled by flights?", wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    origin_destination_counts = data.groupby(['origin', 'destination']).size().unstack(fill_value=0)
    
    ax = plt.gca()
    im = ax.imshow(origin_destination_counts, cmap='viridis')
    
    ax.set_xticks(range(len(origin_destination_counts.columns)))
    ax.set_yticks(range(len(origin_destination_counts.index)))
    ax.set_xticklabels(origin_destination_counts.columns)
    ax.set_yticklabels(origin_destination_counts.index)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.setp(ax.get_xticklabels(), rotation=45, ha="right", rotation_mode="anchor")
    
    plt.xlabel('Destination')
    plt.ylabel('Origin')
    plt.title('Which origin and destination pairs have the highest number of flights?', wrap=True)
    
    plt.colorbar(im, ax=ax)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    date_counts = data['date'].value_counts().sort_index()
    
    plt.plot(date_counts.index, date_counts.values)
    
    ax = plt.gca()
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    plt.title("What is the distribution of flight dates?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    box_plot_data = data.groupby('origin')['delay'].apply(list)
    
    plt.boxplot(box_plot_data, vert=True, patch_artist=True)
    plt.xticks(range(1, len(box_plot_data.index) + 1), box_plot_data.index)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("What is the distribution of flight delays by origin?")
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
